1) Identify at least 3 real-world applications and specify

a) Online Streaming Platform(netfix,amazon)
 
 Database Type: NoSql (Cassandra)
 Suitable :
 Handles massive user data and viewing history.
 Highly scalable to support millions of users simultaneously.
 Optimized for high read performance.
 Works well with distributed systems across regions.
 
 b) Ride-Sharing Application(uber,ola)
 
 Database Type: NoSql+In-memory (mongodb)
 Suitable :
 NoSQL manages trip data, drivers, and users.
 In-memory DB handles real-time location tracking.
 Fast response for ride matching and fare calculation.
 Scales easily during peak hours.


c) Healthcare Management System

  Database Type:SQL Database(MySql, PostgreSQL)
  Suitable :
  Stores highly structured and sensitive data.
  Ensures data accuracy and consistency.
  Supports complex queries for patient history.
  Complies with data integrity and security standards.
  
d) Online Learning Platform(Corsera/Udemy)

 Database Type:In-Memory Database(Redis)
 Suitable:
 Requires ultra-fast access for player stats and game state.
 Low latency for real-time multiplayer interaction.
 Improves game responsiveness.
 Handles frequent updates efficiently.

